'''Osakai''' is a village in [[Lower Dir District]] of the [[Khyber Pakhtunkhwa]] province of Pakistan. Osakai is divided into Osakai Bala and Osakai Payeen. It comes under Union Council Kotigram and under Tehsil Adenzai.
Osakai as a whole consist of Karimabad, Dagai, Ghwandai, Qazi Abad and Lowarha.
Osakai as a whole consist of Karimabad, Dagai, Ghwandai, Qazi Abad and Lowarha.
Osakai has a hospital unit (BHU), Government high school for Girls and also a Government high school for Boys. Osakai has some historical places i.e kafir kot, sroo manroo ( red fort) and also many picnic spots i.e osakai waterfall, Khan baba, Bar charhay, small water dams. Osakai is famous for stone slabs. It can be used for graves and savage system .
